				\begin{document}$${I}_{\perp }$$\end{document} largely decreases at 45° and reaches zero at 90° light incident angle, which is much smaller than that at the hemispherical surface. The integrated I⊥\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
