				\begin{document}$${I}_{\perp }$$\end{document} flux from different incident angles is calculated in Fig. 1c, and the incident flux at the hemispherical surface is always higher than the planar one. Therefore, the hemispherical photodetectors can collect more information regarding different incident directions of light, which is more convenient for wider vision or object positioning.Fig. 1The effective incident flux intensity on hemispherical and planar surface, and thick perovskite films by spray-coating.
